gomodel:SYNGO_4773  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4, 8: immunoEM showed neurexophilin-1 (Nxph1) localization to the synaptic clefts of symmetric (inhibitory) and asymmetric, presumably excitatory, synapses.\n\nNote that neurexophilin-1 (Nxph1) is only expressed in a subpopulation of neurons, as also described by Missler M, et al. 1998 (PMID:9570794).. Experimental description: Figure 4: \"Several Nxph1-GFPtg/+ transgenic mouse lines express the fusion protein as evidenced by immunoblots of brain lysates.\"\n\nSI Materials and Methods:\n\"For overexpression of Nxph1- GFP under the Thy1.2 promoter, a transgenic vector was constructed using plasmid pCMVD2 [full-length Nxph1 (3)]. EGFP was inserted (junctional amino acid sequence: Nxph1 . . . PYFPSGPGPG MVSKGEE ...EGFP... GMDELYKPG stop . . . Nxph1 3 ' -UTR) and transferred to pEX21 (4) to generate pThyNxph1C ' EGFP.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4773" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

